Accounting from July 1, 1981, whether or not the trust was in existence at that time, commissions are payable at the end of each year upon the fair value of the corpus or principal held in trust at the end of each year as follows:
Four tenths of one percent on the first $250,000;
One fourth of one percent on the next $250,000;
Three twentieths of one percent on the next $500,000; and
One tenth of one percent upon any excess. Corpus commissions shall be paid out of and chargeable against the corpus.
